<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>RubriCheck AI | Assignment Feedback with RAG</title>
  <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/images/RubriCheck%20Logo.png">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <%- include('partials/header', { activePage: 'home', landingAnchors: true }) %>

  <main class="landing-page">
    <section class="landing-hero" id="top">
      <div class="container landing-hero-grid">
        <div class="hero-copy-block reveal-on-scroll">
          <p class="eyebrow">
            <span class="eyebrow-icon">AI</span>
            RAG-powered assignment review for students
          </p>
          <h1>RubriCheck AI</h1>
          <p class="hero-tagline">Know what to improve before you submit.</p>
          <p class="hero-copy">
            RubriCheck AI compares your assignment brief, marking rubric, and student draft.
            It retrieves the most relevant rubric context with ChromaDB, asks Gemini to analyse it,
            then returns structured feedback, checklist items, lecturer questions, and reminder support.
          </p>

          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="btn btn-primary" href="#demo">Analyze Assignment</a>
            <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="#how-it-works">See Workflow</a>
          </div>

          <div class="hero-proof-row" aria-label="RubriCheck AI strengths">
            <span>Gemini feedback</span>
            <span>ChromaDB retrieval</span>
            <span>Telegram reminders</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <article class="hero-product-panel reveal-on-scroll" aria-label="RubriCheck AI feedback preview">
          <div class="preview-topbar">
            <div class="window-dots" aria-hidden="true">
              <span class="dot red"></span>
              <span class="dot yellow"></span>
              <span class="dot green"></span>
            </div>
            <strong>Live Rubric Review</strong>
          </div>

          <div class="hero-score-layout">
            <div class="score-panel">
              <p class="panel-label">Readiness</p>
              <div class="score-ring">
                <span>78</span>
                <small>/ 100</small>
              </div>
              <p class="score-caption">Review before submission</p>
            </div>

            <div class="rubric-panel">
              <p class="panel-label">Rubric Coverage</p>
              <div class="rubric-row">
                <div class="rubric-label">
                  <span>Problem Analysis</span>
                  <strong>86%</strong>
                </div>
                <div class="progress-track"><span class="progress-fill green" style="width: 86%;"></span></div>
              </div>
              <div class="rubric-row">
                <div class="rubric-label">
                  <span>Evidence Quality</span>
                  <strong>64%</strong>
                </div>
                <div class="progress-track"><span class="progress-fill blue" style="width: 64%;"></span></div>
              </div>
              <div class="rubric-row">
                <div class="rubric-label">
                  <span>Referencing</span>
                  <strong>52%</strong>
                </div>
                <div class="progress-track"><span class="progress-fill orange" style="width: 52%;"></span></div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="hero-feedback-card">
            <span class="mini-icon">AI</span>
            <div>
              <strong>Top priority</strong>
              <p>Add clearer evidence for the rubric criterion on justification and impact.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="landing-section split-section" id="about">
      <div class="container split-grid">
        <div class="section-heading align-left reveal-on-scroll">
          <p class="section-kicker">About the Project</p>
          <h2>Students need clearer feedback before the deadline, not after grades are released.</h2>
          <p>
            Assignment rubrics can be detailed, but students often struggle to translate each criterion
            into concrete improvements. RubriCheck AI turns uploaded documents into a practical review
            session, helping students find weak areas, understand rubric expectations, and plan final edits.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mini-metric-grid reveal-on-scroll">
          <article>
            <span>01</span>
            <h3>Problem</h3>
            <p>Students miss hidden rubric requirements and submit drafts without a clear readiness check.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <span>02</span>
            <h3>Solution</h3>
            <p>AI reviews the draft against the brief and rubric, then returns specific next steps.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <span>03</span>
            <h3>Why AI</h3>
            <p>Gemini can summarise, compare, explain, and generate follow-up guidance from the documents.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <span>04</span>
            <h3>Benefits</h3>
            <p>Students get faster revision decisions, better preparation, and fewer last-minute mistakes.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="landing-section" id="features">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-heading reveal-on-scroll">
          <p class="section-kicker">Features</p>
          <h2>One workflow for review, revision, practice, and reminders</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-grid presentation-grid">
          <article class="feature-card reveal-on-scroll">
            <span class="feature-icon blue">UP</span>
            <h3>Assignment Analysis</h3>
            <p>Processes the assignment brief, rubric, and draft in one upload flow.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="feature-card reveal-on-scroll">
            <span class="feature-icon mint">RB</span>
            <h3>Rubric Checking</h3>
            <p>Maps feedback to rubric expectations so students know what matters.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="feature-card reveal-on-scroll">
            <span class="feature-icon purple">AI</span>
            <h3>AI Feedback</h3>
            <p>Uses Gemini to generate readable strengths, gaps, priorities, and recommendations.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="feature-card reveal-on-scroll">
            <span class="feature-icon green">CL</span>
            <h3>Before-Submission Checklist</h3>
            <p>Turns feedback into concrete checks students can complete before uploading.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="feature-card reveal-on-scroll">
            <span class="feature-icon violet">Q</span>
            <h3>Lecturer Question Generator</h3>
            <p>Creates likely viva or presentation questions from the feedback and documents.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="feature-card reveal-on-scroll">
            <span class="feature-icon orange">TG</span>
            <h3>Telegram Reminder Integration</h3>
            <p>Prepares reminder details for n8n automation and Telegram notifications.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="feature-card reveal-on-scroll">
            <span class="feature-icon blue">RAG</span>
            <h3>RAG-powered Document Analysis</h3>
            <p>Stores document chunks in ChromaDB and retrieves relevant context for Gemini.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="feature-card reveal-on-scroll">
            <span class="feature-icon mint">ETH</span>
            <h3>Ethical AI Guidance</h3>
            <p>Positions AI feedback as a learning guide, not a replacement for student work.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="landing-section workflow-section" id="how-it-works">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-heading reveal-on-scroll">
          <p class="section-kicker">How It Works</p>
          <h2>A clear AI pipeline from upload to action</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="workflow-grid reveal-on-scroll" aria-label="RubriCheck AI workflow">
          <article><span>1</span><h3>Upload Files</h3><p>Brief, rubric, and draft are submitted through the existing upload route.</p></article>
          <article><span>2</span><h3>Extract Text</h3><p>The backend reads supported PDF, DOCX, and TXT documents.</p></article>
          <article><span>3</span><h3>Retrieve Context</h3><p>RAG searches ChromaDB for rubric and document chunks relevant to the draft.</p></article>
          <article><span>4</span><h3>Gemini Analysis</h3><p>Gemini compares the retrieved evidence and produces structured feedback.</p></article>
          <article><span>5</span><h3>Student Feedback</h3><p>Results appear as scores, priorities, weak areas, checklist items, and report downloads.</p></article>
          <article><span>6</span><h3>Reminders</h3><p>Students can enable Telegram reminders through the n8n reminder workflow.</p></article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="landing-section demo-section" id="demo">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-heading reveal-on-scroll">
          <p class="section-kicker">Demo</p>
          <h2>Upload documents and run the real AI analysis flow</h2>
          <p>This form uses the existing `/check-assignment` route, Gemini integration, RAG retrieval, and upload handling.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="demo-grid">
          <div class="homepage-upload-card reveal-on-scroll">
            <%- include('partials/uploadForm', { error: typeof error === 'undefined' ? null : error }) %>
          </div>

          <aside class="feedback-preview-stack reveal-on-scroll" aria-label="AI feedback preview">
            <article class="feedback-dashboard-card compact-card">
              <div class="section-title-row">
                <span class="section-icon blue" aria-hidden="true">AI</span>
                <div>
                  <h3>AI Feedback Preview</h3>
                  <p>After upload, the generated report displays as structured cards.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="feedback-metric-grid demo-metric-grid">
                <article class="feedback-stat-card">
                  <span>Completion</span>
                  <strong class="blue-text">80%</strong>
                  <div class="stat-progress"><span style="width: 80%;"></span></div>
                </article>
                <article class="feedback-stat-card">
                  <span>Readiness</span>
                  <strong class="green-text">75%</strong>
                  <div class="stat-progress green"><span style="width: 75%;"></span></div>
                </article>
              </div>
            </article>

            <article class="chat-preview-card">
              <div class="section-title-row">
                <span class="section-icon purple" aria-hidden="true">Q</span>
                <div>
                  <h3>Follow-up AI Chat Assistant</h3>
                  <p>Available below the generated feedback and powered by the existing Gemini follow-up endpoint.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="suggestion-chip-row">
                <span>What should I improve first?</span>
                <span>Explain this rubric criterion.</span>
                <span>Why is my readiness low?</span>
                <span>How can I improve my introduction?</span>
              </div>
              <div class="chat-input-preview" aria-hidden="true">
                <span>Ask about your generated feedback...</span>
                <strong>Send</strong>
              </div>
            </article>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="landing-section reminder-flow-section" id="reminders">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-heading reveal-on-scroll">
          <p class="section-kicker">Reminder Integration</p>
          <h2>From AI feedback to deadline action</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="reminder-flow reveal-on-scroll">
          <article><span>AI</span><h3>AI Feedback</h3><p>RubriCheck identifies priorities and checklist items.</p></article>
          <article><span>ON</span><h3>Enable Reminder</h3><p>Student confirms deadline and Telegram Chat ID.</p></article>
          <article><span>N8N</span><h3>n8n Automation</h3><p>The reminder workflow prepares scheduled messages.</p></article>
          <article><span>TG</span><h3>Telegram Reminder</h3><p>Students receive deadline reminders before submission.</p></article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="landing-section tech-section" id="technology">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-heading reveal-on-scroll">
          <p class="section-kicker">Technology Stack</p>
          <h2>Built with a practical full-stack AI architecture</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="tech-grid reveal-on-scroll">
          <span>Google Gemini</span>
          <span>RAG</span>
          <span>ChromaDB</span>
          <span>Node.js</span>
          <span>Express</span>
          <span>n8n</span>
          <span>MySQL</span>
          <span>HTML</span>
          <span>CSS</span>
          <span>JavaScript</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="landing-section team-section" id="team">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-heading reveal-on-scroll">
          <p class="section-kicker">Team</p>
          <h2>Final-year AI project presentation</h2>
          <p>RubriCheck AI was built for C240 AI Essentials and Innovations as a student-focused rubric review system.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="team-grid reveal-on-scroll">
          <article><span>RC</span><h3>RubriCheck Team</h3><p>AI workflow, web application, reminder automation, and presentation build.</p></article>
          <article><span>C240</span><h3>Module</h3><p>C240 AI Essentials and Innovations.</p></article>
          <article><span>AI</span><h3>Project Focus</h3><p>Responsible use of AI to support learning, revision, and submission readiness.</p></article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer class="site-footer">
    <div class="container footer-content">
      <div class="footer-brand">
        <img class="footer-logo" src="/images/RubriCheck%20Logo.png" alt="RubriCheck AI logo">
        <strong>RubriCheck AI</strong>
      </div>
      <p>RubriCheck Team | C240 AI Essentials and Innovations | &copy; 2026 RubriCheck AI.</p>
    </div>
  </footer>

  <script src="/js/script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
